    {
      "id": "knowledge-research-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Knowledge / Research Nodeset",
      "position": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": -430
      },
      "width": 500,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Knowledge / Research Nodeset\n\nCandidate types from the source board:\n- `concept`\n- `claim`\n- `evidence`\n- `source`\n- `question`\n- `definition`\n- `example`\n- `counterpoint`\n- `summary`\n- `citation-note`\n\nThis family matters if Twilite wants research graphs to preserve provenance, synthesis, and argument structure instead of flattening everything into markdown plus loose references.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
